


QLS Linux Engineer Training Program
In this course, you will master Linux installation, configuration, administration, troubleshooting, the command line, OS tools, and much more. By the end of this course, you will be a professional Linux Systems Administrator eligible to apply for various Linux and other techincal roles. You will also be able to take the RedHat exam to become a RedHat Certified System Administrator (RHCSA).

Linux is an open-source operating system with a community of collaborators who communicate with other developers to develop and implement system enhancements and vulnerabilities. Linux is the number one operating system for the corporate world (think of Google). Nearly 80% of all web servers are powered by Linux with the average salary of a Linux SysAdmin being six-figures.




